The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered remarks at a meeting with law enforcement officials involved in the High Intensity Drug Trafficking Area (HIDTA) program. He praised their efforts in combating drug abuse and addiction and expressed gratitude on behalf of the President and the administration. Pence highlighted the administration's commitment to supporting law enforcement and combating the flow of illegal drugs into the country. He also emphasized the importance of securing the southern border and called for the construction of a border wall. Pence assured the officials of the administration's continued support and concluded by expressing prayers for their safety and success in their mission.